Basics of coordinates on the screen:        
	0                      x
      0 +--------------------->
        |
	|
	|
	|
	|
      y v

Map character conventions:
	Map:
		S : Sea
		P : Plain
		W : Wood
		M : Mountain
	Spawn:
		Blue / Red
		I / i: Infantry
		M / m: Mechanized Infantry
		T / t: Tank
		D / d: Mobile Artillery
		A / a: Anti-Air
		F / f: Fighter
		B / b: Bomber
		C / c: Battle Copter

1. Create Object 
	Arguments:
		String: Map options
2. loadMap
	Arguments:
		String: Path to map (.csv)
3. drawMap
	Arguments:
		2D ArrayList: Position of each troop
		2D ArrayList: Marked fields
		Int: X position of current troop
		Int: Y position of current troop

4. setText
	Arguments:
		Int: Position of text
		String: Actual text
		String:	Color of text
	Info: Possible positions
		+-----------------------+
		|0                     1|
		|                       |
		|	    2           |
		|                       |
		|3                     4|
		+-----------------------+

5. removeText
	Arguments:
		Int: Position of text
6. getTerrain
	Arguments:
		Int: X position of wanted Terrain
		Int: Y position of wanted Terrain
